value.name: Breach discovered in dam at Lake Waxhoma, crews work to repair damage
value.description: Crews are continuing to work to repair a breach in a dam at Lake Waxhoma. It’s in Osage County, about a couple of miles east of Barnsdall. Water is rapidly flowing into Little Dog Thrasher creek from the dam.

value.name: Barnsdall Mayor: Breach At Lake Waxhoma Dam Fixed Temporarily, Situation Under Control
value.description: BARNSDALL, Oklahoma - Crews worked through the night at the Lake Waxhoma Dam in Osage County, trying to fill a hole that was discovered on Wednesday. Barnsdall Mayor Johnny Kelley

video.name: Barnsdall Mayor: Breach At Lake Waxhoma Dam Fixed Temporarily, Situation Under Control

value.name: Barnsdall Police: Breach Reported At Lake Waxhoma Dam
value.description: The Barnsdall Police Chief said there has been a breach in the Lake Waxhoma dam. Officials have restricted all access and roads to the dam except for emergency crews as they work to fix the leak. The breach was discovered this morning near the very bottom of the dam.
